SQL_STMT_U.val: SELECT BTCP_HYPA_ID from :1 where BTCP_BTCH_ID = :2 and BTCP_STATUS = 0 FOR FETCH ONLY OPTIMIZE FOR 100 ROWS

Text.val: This task is relevant for multiuser environment
If one User located on a BATCH row and an other User located on the
same BATCH row and pressed Button OK --> GOTO OPH202A,
payments details, the actual view for the User who still located on
BATCH row, is not updated. He could also press Button OK and could
modfify the related BATCH_PAYMENT rows.
THIS IS NOT ALLOWED!!!
So we first have to look, if the BATCH row is locked=BTCH_ACTIVE_USER<>''
If it's locked, the actual screen will be refreshed.
-- batch could be handeld by user --> no lock exists
-- batch locked, handling of batch not possible
-- batch could not be handeld by user --> all payments are already handled
-- batch already handled, handling not possible
-- Transaction will be opened, see DB table
